    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Genus of small dog-sized animals representing the oldest known horse; they lived in the Eocene Epoch. Characterized by a relatively short face, eye sockets nearer the middle than modern horses, and a short  space between the front teeth and the cheek teeth (diastema).</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
